As security situation in the state improves, the Kaduna State Government has reviewed curfew hours throughout the 23 LGAs of the state. In a statement on Wednesday, the Commissioner, Ministry of Internal Security and Home Affairs, Mr. Samuel Aruwan, said, “From Thursday, 29th October 2020, citizens can move and pursue their lawful business from 6am to 6pm. “Movement is restricted during the night-time curfew hours of 6pm to 6am. “Government appeals to residents of the state to remain vigilant, report criminals and continue to operate with the security agencies,” the statement said